[2] Fiji
Date: Tue, 17 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Fiji Times [edited]
<http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?id=26676>

Students hospitalized for typhoid
-----------------------------------
11 students from Ratu Luke Primary and Ratu Luke Secondary School are still
admitted at the Nabouwalu hospital with suspected typhoid. Despite hospital
authorities in Nabouwalu refusing to divulge any information on the
progress of the students, school manager Eroni Tabakece said they are still
admitted at the hospital.
Blood samples and water samples were also taken from the school but results
of the tests are still pending. The students' stools were taken to Labasa
hospital for tests. Last week, the school was forced to close after 11
students were admitted at the Nabouwalu hospital suffering from suspected
typhoid.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It seems that not all of the student cases are likely to be typhoid
infection. Indeed, even without bloody diarrhea -- which is much more
suggestive of shigellosis or amoebiasis -- constipation is often more
prominent than diarrhea in typhoid fever. - Mod.LL]
